[[File:Border Inn Sign Utah Nevada September 2013.JPG|thumb|right|Border Inn Sign]] The '''Border Inn''' is a [[motel]] on the [[Utah]]/[[Nevada]] border in [[Baker, Nevada]] on [[U.S. 6]]/[[U.S. 50]]. It is located near [[Great Basin National Park]]. The motel offers round-the-clock service and the regular hours are 12:00 am - 11:59 pm from Monday to Sunday. <references group="Border Inn Hours, Locations and Phone Number" /><references group="1. Border Inn Hours, Locations and Phone Numbers" /> <references />This motel is unique because while the motel rooms are in Utah, and on [[Mountain Time Zone|Mountain Time]], the office, restaurant, and casino are in Nevada, and [[Pacific Time Zone|Pacific Time]]. The motel also serves as the housing facilities for the seasonal park rangers of the nearby Great Basin National Park.
