{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} {{Use British English|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Young Sherlock: The Mystery of the Manor House | image = The Mystery of the Manor House Capture.png | caption = | show_name_2 = | genre = | creator = | developer = | writer = | director = | creative_director = | presenter = | starring = [[Guy Henry (actor)|Guy Henry]] | judges = | voices = | narrated = | theme_music_composer = | opentheme = | endtheme = | composer = | country = UK<ref>[http://www.sherlock-holmes.org.uk/world/television.php The wide world of Sherlock Holmes]</ref> | language = English | num_seasons = <!-- or num_series --> | num_episodes = | list_episodes = | executive_producer = | producer = | editor = | location = | cinematography = | camera = | runtime = | company = | distributor = [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] | channel = <!-- or network --> | picture_format = | audio_format = | first_run = | first_aired = 31 October 1982 | last_aired = | status = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | related = | website = | website_title = | production_website = }}
'''''Young Sherlock: The Mystery of the Manor House''''' is an 8-episode television series about the youthful years of [[Sherlock Holmes]]. The show was produced by [[Granada Television]] and premiered on 31 October 1982. Although there was no televised sequel to this story, Gerald Frow penned a follow-up for Granada's [[The Dragon Book (anthology)|Dragon Books]] (who in 1982 published his novelisation of this tale). ''Young Sherlock: The Adventure at Ferryman's Creek'' went on sale in 1984.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0271933/ Young Sherlock: The Mystery of the Manor House at the Internet Movie Database]</ref>
==Plot== Until [[Dr. Watson]] listened to the [[Dictaphone|dictaphone cylinders]] Sherlock recorded in his retirement, not even he knew "The Mystery of Manor House." It's the strange happenings at his former childhood home that transform Sherlock ([[Guy Henry (actor)|Guy Henry]]) from a brilliant and curious 17-year-old schoolboy to a brilliant and accomplished detective. Young Sherlock is the suspenseful eight episode series chronicling "The Mystery of the Manor House." The year is 1871. A [[typhoid]] epidemic forces Sherlock to come home early. What he encounters is anything but a happy homecoming. Mysterious happenings start swirling around Sherlock from the moment he steps foot on the [[Manor house|manor grounds]]. Residents masquerade as honourable. Poison, deceit and greed fill the air. Sherlock's powerful deductive reasoning skills are put to the test. A priceless [[diamond]] will vanish unless Sherlock can foil a conspiracy against [[Queen Victoria]].<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/Young-Sherlock-Mystery-Manor-House/dp/B00008J2I9 Young Sherlock - The Mystery of the Manor House DVD] at [[Amazon.com|Amazon]]</ref>
==Cast== *[[Guy Henry (actor)|Guy Henry]] as [[Sherlock Holmes]] *[[June Barry]] as Mrs. Turnbull *[[Tim Brierley]] as John Whitney *[[Heather Chasen]] as Aunt Rachel *[[John Fraser (actor)|John Fraser]] as Uncle Gideon *[[Christopher Villiers]] as Jasper Moran *[[Eva Griffith]] as Charity
